  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And Jehoahaz besought the Lord, and the Lord hearkened unto him,.... He did not apply in his distress to the calves he worshipped, but to the Lord; who had a regard to his prayer, not for his sake, or any righteousness of his, or even his repentance and humiliation, which were only external; but for the sake of Israel, and because they were oppressed, who were his people, and he their God, though they had sadly departed from him: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "for he saw the oppression of Israel; not only with his eye of omniscience, but with an eye of mercy and compassion: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "because the king of Syria oppressed them; by his incursions upon them, and wars with them. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "because the king of Syria oppressed them; by his incursions upon them, and wars with them. ",
            "children": []
          },
